"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723019","Department of Health","false","2017-04-25","<p>Data on the numbers of people diagnosed with familial hypercholesterolemia in England and local commissioning organisations is not centrally held.</p><p> </p><p>Public Health England has established the National Congenital Anomaly and Rare Disease Registration Service (NCARDRS) which brings together data from existing regional and disease specific registries into a single register. A certain form of familial hypercholesterolemia - homozygous FH - is classified as a rare disease and so is included in NCARDRS. Further information can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/the-national-congenital-anomaly-and-rare-disease-registration-service-ncardrs" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/guidance/the-national-congenital-anomaly-and-rare-disease-registration-service-ncardrs</a></p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-04-25T12:29:43.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723019/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723019/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723019/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-20","Familial Hypercholesterolaemia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people were diagnosed with familial hypercholesterolemia in (a) England and (b) each local commissioning organisation in 2016.17.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","71527"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723020","Home Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>In line with the Public Appointments Governance Code that was published on 16 December 2016, there is no plan to publish the terms or outcome of the performance appraisal for the Independent Anti-Slavery Commissioner.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-04-26T09:32:23.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723020/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723020/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723020/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-20","Independent Anti-Slavery Commissioner","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 18 April 2017 to Question 69878, whether the terms and outcome of the performance appraisal for the Independent Anti-Slavery Commissioner will be published.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","71480"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723021","Home Office","false","2017-04-25","<p>The Department’s plans for immigration enforcement will be communicated in due course.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-04-25T12:21:01.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723021/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723021/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723021/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-20","Immigration Enforcement Directorate","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when she plans for the Immigration Enforcement Business Plan for 2016-17 to be published.","false","Biography information for Dr Sarah Wollaston","Totnes","Dr Sarah Wollaston","71513"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723022","Home Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>I refer the honourable member to my response to PQ 47658, submitted to Parliament on 19 October 2016.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-04-27T09:33:54.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723022/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723022/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723022/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-20","Immigrants: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much her Department has paid in compensation for unlawful immigration detention since figures on such compensation payments were published in 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Dr Sarah Wollaston","Totnes","Dr Sarah Wollaston","71514"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723023","Home Office","false","2017-04-25","<p>The Home Office does not comment on individual cases. The Home Secretary can deprive individuals of their citizenship where it is conducive to the public good to do so.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-04-25T12:28:48.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723023/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723023/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723023/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-20","Asma al-Assad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether her Department has made an assessment of whether recent statements and implications by Asma al-Assad, wife of the Syrian President, was conducted in a manner suitable for her UK citizenship.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","71477"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723024","Home Office","false","2017-04-25","<p>Decisions about how policing resources are best deployed are for Chief Constables and democratically accountable Police and Crime Commissioners. They are responsible for ensuring the needs of the local community are met. I welcome the work of the Police Reform and Transformation Board, at a national level, in seeking to establish a local policing sub group which will bring together a variety of stakeholders to help to deliver the Policing Vision 2025.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-04-25T11:54:06.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723024/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723024/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723024/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-20","Community Policing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will work with (a) HM Inspectorate of Constabulary, (b) the College of Policing, (c) the National Police Chiefs Council and (d) the Association of Police and Crime Commissioners to draw up a national action plan to ensure the protection of community policing functions across the country.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","71465"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723025","Home Office","false","2017-04-25","<p>Her Majesty’s Inspectorate of Constabulary’s (HMIC’s) recommendations are primarily for police leaders to take action and ensure progress is made. In its Effectiveness report, published on 2 March 2017, HMIC called on the National Police Chiefs’ Council, working with the College of Policing, to review by June what is being done to tackle concerns over the number of police detectives. HMIC recommended that these bodies should put in place a national action plan by December 2017.</p><p> </p><p>We continue to work with national policing leads to encourage better analysis of this issue and the development of sustainable solutions.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-04-25T11:59:40.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723025/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723025/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723025/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-20","Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will work with (a) HM Inspectorate of Constabulary, (b) the College of Policing, (c) the National Police Chiefs Council and (d) the Association of Police and Crime Commissioners to draw up a national action plan to increase recruitment and training of police detectives.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","71464"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723026","Home Office","false","2017-04-25","<p>EU nationals have a right to reside in the UK for more than three months if they are workers, self-employed, jobseekers, self-sufficient persons or students, are a family member of an EU national or have acquired a right of permanent residence in EU law. Under EU law, self-sufficient persons and students are required to hold comprehensive sickness insurance. The Home Office does not hold any information on the number of citizens from other EU Member states who do not have comprehensive sickness insurance.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-04-25T12:19:41.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723026/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723026/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723026/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-20","EU Nationals: Health Insurance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many citizens from other EU countries with the right to reside in the UK before 29 March 2017 do not have private medical insurance.","false","Biography information for Heidi Allen","South Cambridgeshire","Heidi Allen","71489"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723027","Home Office","false","2017-04-25","<p>The paper, “Reshaping Policing for the Public”, was intended to stimulate discussion on the future of policing, concluding that “the police service must go further in changing itself so that it continues to achieve its primary goal of preventing crime and keeping the public safe”. Since the publication of this paper, the Government has provided support to the policing sector to enable it to become self-reforming. This includes the Police Transformation Fund (PTF) which provides Police and Crime Commissioners with a real opportunity to transform policing and it is incentivising policing to meet future challenges by being more efficient and effective. The Police Reform and Transformation Board makes recommendations to the Home Secretary about how to spend the PTF.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-04-25T12:03:48.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723027/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723027/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723027/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-20","Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 4 April 2017 to Question 69588, on police, which recommendations contained in the Reshaping Policing for the Public report her Department (a) plans to implement and (b) has implemented since that report was published.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","71483"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723028","Home Office","false","2017-04-25","<p>The British public has been very generous in their offers to help and accommodate refugees under the UK’s Resettlement schemes. Many have made offers of housing directly to their local authority or through the Help Refugees in the UK website. We don’t hold information about how many offers of housing are made or taken up by local authorities.</p><p> </p><p>Some community groups are also offering housing for refugees through the Community Sponsorship scheme. This is a new scheme launched in July, for which we do not currently report numbers.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-04-25T12:24:07.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723028/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723028/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723028/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-20","Refugees: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people have offered a home to refugee (a) children and (b) families in the last 12 months; and how many of those offers have been taken up.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","71492"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723029","Home Office","false","2017-04-25","<p>Under Regulation 18(3) of the Immigration (European Economic Area) Regulations 2016, non-EEA nationals who make a valid application for EEA documentation are already issued with a certificate of application.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-04-25T12:22:36.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723029/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723029/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723029/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-20","Entry Clearances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will take steps to enable non-EEA applicants to be issued with a certificate of application.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","71512"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723030","Home Office","false","2017-04-25","<p>The Government keeps the legislation relating to air weapons in England and Wales under review. High-powered air weapons require a firearms licence and low-powered air weapons are already subject to a range of controls, such as the requirement that owners take reasonable precautions to prevent young people from gaining unauthorised access to air weapons. Guidance is published on the safe use and storage of air weapons and this can be found at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/117804/air-weapons-safety-leaflet.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/117804/air-weapons-safety-leaflet.pdf</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-04-25T11:56:10.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723030/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723030/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723030/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-20","Airguns","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of the potential merits of introducing a compulsory trigger lock on air rifles; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Karin Smyth","Bristol South","Karin Smyth","71502"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723031","Home Office","false","2017-04-25","<p>This is a matter for the Police and Crime Commissioner for the West Midlands.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-04-25T08:24:48.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723031/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723031/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723031/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-20","West Midlands Police: Accenture","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of the effect of West Midlands Police Force's Innovation and Integration partnership with Accenture on (a) crime prevention and (b) the pace of response to reported crimes in that area.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","71395"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723032","Home Office","false","2017-04-25","<p>Decisions relating to police stations and other estates are a matter for the Metropolitan Police Service, working with the Mayor's Office for Policing and Crime.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-04-25T08:25:46.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723032/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723032/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723032/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-20","Police Stations: Harrow","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what discussions she has had on the closure of Harrow Police Station; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","71421"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723033","Home Office","false","2017-04-25","<p>We expect police to investigate all crimes that are reported to them. All forces will suspend crime investigations if, after initial investigation, they conclude that there are no further lines of enquiry to pursue because there is no evidence trail or witnesses. These decisions are an operational matter for forces, but investigations can be reopened at any time should further evidence come to light.</p><p> </p><p>The Home Office collects and publishes quarterly data on crime outcomes recorded by the police.</p><p> </p><p>The latest available data are published in the ‘Crime Outcomes in England and Wales, year to September 2016’ data tables, available here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/crime-outcomes-in-england-and-wales-year-to-september-2016-data-tables" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/crime-outcomes-in-england-and-wales-year-to-september-2016-data-tables</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-04-25T12:06:41.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723033/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723033/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723033/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-20","Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many reported crimes have led to no further action being taken by police in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","71422"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723034","Home Office","false","2017-04-25","<p>The Home Office collects and publishes data biannually on the number of police officers and police staff employed by each police force. These data can be found in the ‘Police Workforce, England and Wales’ statistical bulletins.</p><p> </p><p>The latest statistics, representing the picture as at 30 September 2016, can be found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-workforce-england-and-wales-30-september-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-workforce-england-and-wales-30-september-2016</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-04-25T11:49:33.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723034/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723034/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723034/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-20","Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many (a) police officers and (b) policing staff were employed in each force in England and Wales in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","71423"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723035","Home Office","false","2017-04-25","<p>The Home Office collect and publish data on the number of arrests for notifiable offences, by police force area, on an annual basis. Data can be found in the ‘Police Powers and Procedures’ statistical bulletin and accompanying tables, the latest of which can be accessed here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2016</a></p><p> </p><p>The Home Office does not hold information on the number of arrests that led to a prosecution or conviction. Data on prosecutions and convictions are the responsibility of the Ministry of Justice. Data on arrests cannot be linked to prosecution and conviction data.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-04-25T11:47:42.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723035/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723035/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723035/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-20","Arrests","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many arrests have been made in each year since 2010; and how many have led to (a) prosecution and (b) conviction in each of those years.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","71424"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723036","Cabinet Office","false","2017-04-25","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-04-25T14:29:45.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723036/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723036/answer","PQ 71425 v.02.pdf","PQ 71425 v.02.pdf","UKSA Response to PQ71425","UKSA Response to PQ71425","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723036/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-04-20","Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of the number of unreported crimes in England and Wales in 2016.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","71425"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723037","Department for International Development","false","2017-04-25","<p>We have not discussed the content of this particular programme with the Palestinian Authority (PA). The UK deplores any promotion of violence against women and girls. The UK assess the PA’s commitment to gender equality, including tackling domestic violence, through their adherence to the UK Partnership Principles and we raise concerns where appropriate. As part of our Security and Justice programme we have supported the PA to tackle violence against women through training specialised public prosecutors and judges and developing specialised units that cater to female victims of violence.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-04-25T12:03:09.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723037/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723037/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723037/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-04-20","Palestinians: Domestic Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Memorandum of Understanding between the Palestinian Authority and her Department, whether her Department has had discussions with the Palestinian Authority on the content of a programme on Official Palestinian Authority TV, entitled Talk of the Land, broadcast on 1 April 2017, promoting domestic violence.","true","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","71417"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723038","Department for International Development","false","2017-04-25","<p>UK financial assistance to the Palestinian Authority (PA) is only used to fund the salaries of PA health and education public servants in the West Bank who are on a vetted EU list. The list of eligible beneficiaries is subject to a vetting process that includes screening against international and ad hoc sanctions lists, covering a large number of different risk categories including terrorism financing. The UK utterly deplores any violence or intolerance.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-04-25T12:03:55.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723038/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723038/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723038/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-04-20","Hannah Bladon","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps she is taking to ensure that no funding from the public purse is used by the Palestinian Authority to support or assist any person involved in the murder of Hannah Bladon in Jerusalem; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Bob Blackman","Harrow East","Bob Blackman","71426"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723039","Department for International Development","false","2017-04-26","<p>The optimal energy mix of a country depends on a number of contextual factors. DFID assesses these on a case by case basis when deciding how best to support partner governments’ energy strategies, including potential health and environmental impacts.</p><p>International Energy Agency (IEA) analysis suggests that many rural areas can be served at a lower cost by off-grid or mini-grid solutions – such as solar PV, small scale hydropower, and even diesel generators – than by extension of a centralised electricity grid. Coal may offer a cost-effective solution to energy access in some areas that are either connected to a national grid or located close to a grid.</p><p>The UK has a clear policy position to end public funding for both new plants and new investments in existing coal-fired power plants, which has been agreed with the Department of Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy and other government departments. The UK Government will only consider proposals by multilateral development banks for financing coal-fired power plants in the world’s poorest countries where it is clearly demonstrated that no other economically feasible alternative exists, where it fits with the country’s pledged Intended Nationally Determined Contributions (INDCs) and where there is a clear poverty reduction case.</p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-04-26T15:33:50.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723039/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723039/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723039/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-04-20","Developing Countries: Coal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Answer of 31 March 2017 to Question 69479, what assessment her Department has made of the role that coal can play in lifting people in developing countries out of energy poverty.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","71475"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723040","Department for International Development","false","2017-04-26","<p>Assessment of Adhunik Power and Natural Resources power project in Jharkland shows it has a lower cost per megawatt of power generating capacity compared to output of the average solar PV and wind projects in India.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-04-26T15:35:46.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723040/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723040/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723040/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-04-20","India: Electricity Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Answer of 31 March 2017 to Question 69479, what assessment she has made of the cost per megawatt of power generating capacity installed of the investment in Adhunik Power and Natural Resources Ltd power project in Jharkhand compared with other CDC investments in (a) solar PV and (b) wind.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","71476"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723041","Department for International Development","false","2017-04-26","<p>The investment in Adhunik Power represents less than 10 per cent of the total value of CDC’s commitment to the fund.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-04-26T15:34:22.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723041/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723041/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723041/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-04-20","India: Overseas Investment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Answer of 31 March 2017 to Question 69479, how much of CDC's contribution to the India Infrastructure Fund was directed to the 540MW Adhunik Power and Natural Resources Ltd power project in Jharkhand.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","71468"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723042","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-04-25","<p>The Ministry of Justice does not hold information on the number of insurance companies that market car insurance products in the UK.</p><p> </p><p>Leading insurers have publicly committed to pass on savings from the Government’s reforms to consumers through lower premiums, with Axa, Aviva and LV= committing to passing on 100%. Motor insurance is intensely competitive and insurance companies will have little choice but to pass on the savings or risk being priced out of the market. The Government will monitor the industry’s reaction and will consider further action if required.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2017-04-25T14:37:14.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723042/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723042/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723042/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-04-20","Cars: Insurance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many insurance companies market car insurance products in the UK; and which of those insurance companies have declared that they will hand back £40 savings specified by the Government from personal injury reforms to customers in the form of lower premiums.","false","Biography information for Sir George Howarth","Knowsley","Mr George Howarth","71398"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723043","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-04-27","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to the hon. Member in the time available before Prorogation.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-04-27T15:57:08.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723043/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723043/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723043/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-04-20","Reoffenders: Sentencing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the maximum number of offences has been for which a person has been convicted prior to being sent to prison in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","71411"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723044","Prime Minister","false","2017-04-27","<p>None</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2017-04-27T11:55:16.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723044/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723044/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723044/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2017-04-20","Elections: Fraud","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what information she had on the Crown Prosecution Service's decisions on charging hon. Members for election fraud before deciding to call a general election.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","71427"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723045","Department for Transport","false","2017-04-26","<p>The Network Rail Enhancement Delivery Plan sets out the outputs, scope and milestones for projects and ring fenced funds that Network Rail is committed to deliver in the current investment period, 2014-2019. According to the latest version of this plan, published in March 2017, electrification from Manchester to Stalybridge will be ready for entry into service from December 2017.</p><p>The Government has been clear about the affordability and deliverability challenges faced in the current investment programme. In 2015, due to cost increases and schedule delay on important aspects of Network Rail’s investment programme, Sir Peter Hendy was asked to replan the programme to see what could be delivered in an affordable and timely way within the current rail investment period. Following the Hendy Review, the funding available for enhancements is now fixed for the current investment period. A key aspect of this approach has been the ongoing assessment of investment decisions so that we deliver these improvements in a way that provides best value for taxpayers. As such, my Department and Network Rail are currently reviewing the most efficient way to deliver the promised passenger benefits on the important Manchester – Stalybridge – Huddersfield – Leeds – York corridor.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-04-26T10:14:35.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723045/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723045/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723045/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-04-20","Railways: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 4 April 2017 to Question 69245, what the timetables are for works on the electrification of the line between Manchester Victoria and Stalybridge.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","71428"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723046","Department for Transport","false","2017-04-26","<p>While this dispute is for RMT and the train operator to resolve, the Secretary of State and I have made efforts to liaise with Rail North and Arriva Rail North to make sure the operator is limiting the impact of the strikes on passengers.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-04-26T11:12:10.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723046/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723046/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723046/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-04-20","Northern","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to ensure that an agreement is reached relating to the guard guarantee on Northern Rail services.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","71430"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723047","Department for Transport","false","2017-04-25","<p>The Maritime and Coastguard Agency conducted a consultation exercise on the Survey and Inspection Transformation programme to determine the optimum locations for Marine Offices. The output of this consultation exercise identified the retention of an office in the Hull/Beverley area as preferable.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-04-25T14:41:32.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723047/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723047/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723047/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-04-20","Maritime and Coastguard Agency: Beverley","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, for what reasons the Maritime and Coastguard Agency decided to save the Beverley Marine Office from closure; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","71493"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723048","Department for Transport","false","2017-04-25","<p>There have been investigations and assessments carried out to understand the risks posed to the Chilterns Aquifer. This was assessed through the Environmental Impact Assessment process (2013) and reported in the Volume 2, 3 and 5 reports.</p><p> </p><p>Since the Environmental Statement, a programme of ground investigation has been carried out in the Chilterns Aquifer which includes over 300 boreholes, 170 groundwater monitoring locations and 100 aquifer tests.</p><p> </p><p>The ground investigation information has been used for several further local studies across the Colne Valley, the River Misbourne and Wendover. We will continue to work closely with both the Environment Agency and Affinity Water as the design progresses to ensure adequate steps are taken to protect the aquifer.</p><p> </p><p>The specific completed reports and investigations that have taken place on the Chilterns aquifer are as follows:</p><p> </p><p><em>Environmental Statement (2013)</em></p><p> </p><p>As part of the Environmental Statement, impact assessments on the Chilterns Aquifer are presented in the Volume 2, 3 and 5 reports.</p><p> </p><ul><li>Volume 5 – Technical Appendices Water Resources Assessments for CFA6 to CFA11 (WR-002-006 to 11)</li><li>The results of the Volume 5 reports are summarised in the corresponding volume 2 reports for their community forum area.</li><li>Water resources: Route-wide appendix (WR-001-000)</li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p><em>Ground investigation of Chilterns Aquifer</em></p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Investigation</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Undertaken to date</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Further planned</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Boreholes</p></td><td><p>336</p></td><td><p>76</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Groundwater level monitoring locations</p></td><td><p>177</p></td><td><p>31</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Groundwater quality monitoring</p></td><td><p>39</p></td><td><p>25</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Aquifer permeability tests</p></td><td><p>108</p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>In addition to the above since the completion of the Environmental Statement we have completed a Technical Note: Wendover Springs Investigation (12 January 2017). Further studies are in progress regarding the River Misbourne and with Affinity Water.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-04-25T14:29:50.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723048/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723048/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723048/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-04-20","High Speed 2 Railway Line: Chilterns","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will list the reports and investigations that have taken place on the Chilterns Aquifer to establish the level of risk posed to the aquifer by the construction of High Speed 2.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","71490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723049","Department for Transport","false","2017-04-25","<p>As part of the overall Survey and Inspection Transformation Programme, the closure of Tyne Marine Office will save the Maritime and Coastguard Agency (MCA) £88k per annum.</p><p> </p><p>As a direct response to the feedback received during the consultation, the MCA has retained its presence in the north east of England by opening the exam centre in South Tyneside College.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-04-25T14:46:40.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723049/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723049/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723049/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-04-20","Maritime and Coastguard Agency: Port of Tyne","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate his Department has made of the annual saving to the public purse of closing the Maritime and Coastguard Agency's Tyne Marine Office.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","71495"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723050","Home Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>The Government recognises that drink driving is a serious threat to road safety and shares the police’s desire to have roadside evidential breath test instruments available for use as soon as practicably possible. That is why the Home Office, Department for Transport and the police have been working with manufacturers towards the Type Approval of a new generation of Mobile Evidential Breath Test Instruments (MEBTI).</p><p> </p><p>The requirements of Home Office type approval is supported by a stringent and robust process to ensure that evidence from an approved instrument can be relied upon in Court. The ability to type approve also depends on the submission by manufacturers of instruments that meet the technical specification requirements and perform satisfactorily during testing. The Home Office has no control over the maturity of instruments submitted into the type approval process, nor of the performance during testing of any device submitted and therefore no control over the timeframes for type approval.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-04-26T10:50:29.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723050/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723050/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723050/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-20","Breathalysers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the reasons are for the time taken for Home Office Type Approval for mobile evidential breath testing equipment.","false","Biography information for Caroline Flint","Don Valley","Caroline Flint","71463"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723051","Department for Transport","false","2017-04-25","<p>The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy and the Department for Transport have been working closely with wider departments on the preparation of the emissions reduction plan which will set out how we can reduce carbon emissions through the 2020s.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-04-25T14:17:52.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723051/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723051/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723051/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-04-20","Motor Vehicles: Exhaust Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy on the implications of the 2050 Pathways document conclusions on his Department's policy on reducing road traffic.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","71482"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723052","Department for Transport","false","2017-04-26","<p>Network Rail’s Enhancement Delivery Plan update is published quarterly on its website. The Enhancement Delivery Plan was last updated at the end of March 2017 and the next update is due at the end of June 2017.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-04-26T10:28:39.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723052/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723052/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723052/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-04-20","Railways: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 30 March 2017 to Question 69312, when the next Enhancement Delivery Plan quarterly update will be published.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","71449"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723053","Department for Transport","false","2017-04-26","<p>The Secretary of State and I regularly meet with representatives of Network Rail to discuss a wide range of issues, including the delivery of rail electrification between Manchester Victoria and Stalybridge stations.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-04-26T10:33:08.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723053/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723053/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723053/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-04-20","Railways: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 30 March 2017 to Question 69312, on what dates Ministers of his Department have met representatives from Network Rail to discuss the delivery of rail electrification between Manchester Victoria and Stalybridge stations.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","71450"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723054","Department for Transport","false","2017-04-25","<p>I believe that the Honourable Member is referring to the Traffic Management Act 2004. It is true that powers for enforcement of moving traffic contraventions, by local authorities under the Traffic Management Act 2004, have not yet been brought into force outside London (other than the existing powers to enforce contraventions in a bus lane). The Department for Transport’s view is that the Police already have the necessary powers to take action where it is needed. I can confirm that there are no current plans to give local authorities greater powers to enforce moving traffic contraventions.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-04-25T14:50:39.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723054/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723054/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723054/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-04-20","Road Traffic Offences: Cycleways","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans his Department has to commence the provisions of the Road Traffic Act 2004 on the penalties for vehicles encroaching on cycle lanes; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","71460"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723055","Department for Transport","false","2017-04-26","<p>The future capacity of Manchester Piccadilly has been assessed by the train operators, in setting out their plans to meet passenger needs in Manchester through the franchise period. In addition, as part of planning the next control period we are assessing the requirements for passenger capacity into Greater Manchester. Alongside this, Network Rail has applied for a Transport and Works Act Order for the Manchester Piccadilly and Oxford Road Capacity Enhancement scheme. A public inquiry was held in Autumn 2015 concerning the TWA Order application. The Department for Transport is currently considering the application. Network Rail, as the system operator, has been consulted extensively throughout by the Department in order to assess the available capacity at Manchester Piccadilly against the future needs of the current franchises and other operators.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-04-26T10:41:35.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723055/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723055/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723055/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-04-20","Manchester Piccadilly Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 4 April 2017 to Question 69245, if he will list those experts consulted in assessing the future capacity needs of Manchester Piccadilly station.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","71479"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723056","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-04-25","<p>There has not been any analysis of average savings from social tariffs for claimants of employment and support allowance in the work-related activity group.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-04-25T11:48:52.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723056/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723056/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723056/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-04-20","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the average reduction in an individual claimant's personal outgoings he expects to arise from social tariffs for which a claimant of employment and support allowance in the work-related activity group is eligible.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","71517"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723057","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-04-25","<p>Tackling child poverty and disadvantage is a priority for this government. The best route out of poverty is through work and this government has made substantial progress: the number of children in workless households has reduced by 590,000 since 2010. New analysis carried out by my Department shows that children living in families where no one works are significantly more disadvantaged, and achieve poorer outcomes than other children including those living in lower-income working families. This is why <em>Improving Lives: Helping Workless Families</em>, published on 4 April, focuses on tackling the complex barriers faced by many disadvantaged families and provides a framework for a continuing focus on improving their children’s outcomes, now and in the future.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-04-25T14:51:19.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723057/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723057/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723057/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-04-20","Children: Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the Government's policy on child poverty.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","71461"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723058","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-04-25","<p>The best route out of poverty is through work and this government has made substantial progress: both the employment rate at 74.6% and the percentage of children living in working households at 58.3% are at a record high. The Prime Minister has been clear that she is committed to building a country that works for everyone – not just the privileged few.</p><p>That is why this Government has made great efforts to help people into work, reforming the welfare system to make work pay and introducing Universal Credit to strengthen incentives for parents to move into and progress in work. Evidence shows that under Universal Credit claimants move into work significantly faster and stay in work longer than under the old system.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, Universal Credit now provides for 85% of childcare costs giving parents the opportunity to work and earn more, so they can support their families and improve outcomes for their children. We have also announced a 2% reduction in the Universal Credit single taper meaning more support for hardworking families. Around 3 million families across the country will benefit from this change and a couple with two children earning £30,000 a year could benefit by £425 a year.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-04-25T15:32:07.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723058/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723058/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723058/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-04-20","Low Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he is taking to improve the life chances of families in low-paid work.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","71491"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723059","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-04-25","<p>Ministers and officials in the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy meet energy providers and companies to discuss a wide range of issues.</p><p>We are disappointed by the announcements of some companies of price rises when customers on standard variable tariffs are already paying more than they need to.</p><p>We expect energy supply companies to treat all their customers fairly and have made it clear that the energy market should work in the best interests of households and businesses across the country.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-04-25T09:18:45.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723059/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723059/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723059/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-04-20","Energy: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what discussions his Department has had with energy providers and companies on steps to control increases in the price of household energy.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","71393"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723060","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-04-25","<p>The objective of our Industrial Strategy is to improve living standards and economic growth across the whole country. Unquestionably, we want this growth to be sustainable. As we made clear in the Industrial Strategy Green Paper, increasing the sustainability of our economy is not just a necessity, but an opportunity. Britain is well-placed to benefit from the transition to a low-carbon economy, and the Government is committed to working with businesses to make the most of that opportunity.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-04-25T13:15:30.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723060/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723060/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723060/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-04-20","Industry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what account he has made of the potential merits of including sustainability as one of the pillars of his industrial strategy; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","71453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723061","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-04-25","<p>The Committee on Climate Change (CCC), through their annual Progress Reports, provide independent advice on meeting the UK’s carbon budgets. The Government replied to the CCC’s 2016 Progress Report on 13<sup>th</sup> October 2016, and the response can be found at the following address:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/committee-on-climate-changes-2016-progress-report-government-response" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/committee-on-climate-changes-2016-progress-report-government-response</a>.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-04-25T13:15:45.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723061/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723061/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723061/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-04-20","Carbon Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the implications for his Department's policy of meeting the Fifth Carbon Budget of the findings of the 2016 Committee on Climate Change Progress Report.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","71454"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723062","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-04-25","<p>The Government is committed to achieving the UK’s legally binding target to reduce its greenhouse gas emissions by at least 80% below 1990 levels by 2050. When we develop policies and proposals to meet carbon budgets we do so with a view to meeting our 2050 target. We have already made great progress towards our goal, as provisional statistics indicate that UK emissions in 2016 were 42% lower than 1990 and 6% below those in 2015.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-04-25T13:15:56.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723062/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723062/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723062/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-04-20","Greenhouse Gas Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the implications for his Department's policies of the conclusions of the 2050 Pathways work; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","71455"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723063","Women and Equalities","false","2017-04-25","<p>On 28 March the Government issued a public consultation – ‘Caste in Great Britain and Equality Law’ - on the issue of caste and caste discrimination and the Equalities Act 2010.</p><p>The consultation is due to close on 18 July and can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/caste-in-great-britain-and-equality-law-a-public-consulation" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/caste-in-great-britain-and-equality-law-a-public-consulation</a></p><p> </p><p>We encourage all those with an interest in this matter, including employers and entrepreneurs, to contribute to this debate by considering the issues set out in the consultation and responding.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-04-25T15:28:23.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723063/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723063/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723063/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-04-20","Castes: Discrimination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, whether she has consulted employers and entrepreneurs on the potential effect of caste legislation; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","71419"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723064","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-04-25","<p>In 2015 there were 1250 employee jobs in the energy sector in Morecambe and Lunesdale constituency.<sup><sup>[1]</sup></sup></p><p> </p><p>[1] Nomis – ONS Business Register and Employment Survey – using category D</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-04-25T14:01:42.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723064/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723064/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723064/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-04-20","Energy: Morecambe and Lunesdale","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many jobs there are in the energy sector in Morecambe and Lunesdale constituency.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","71415"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723065","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-04-26","<p>Between April 2016 and March 2017, Acas received 24,204 applications for conciliation through the Wages Act jurisdiction.</p><p> </p><p>In the same time period, Acas received 79,375 Helpline calls relating to ‘Wages &amp; National Minimum Wage’. This recording category includes a number of associated wage issues not just failure to pay wages but does not disaggregate complaints from general enquiries. All complaints are forwarded to HM Revenue and Customs (my answer to Question 70317 refers). Acas will provide further advice to callers who work for insolvent companies where enforcement is not an option and to those who would prefer not to be referred for enforcement as they wish to consider their options or pursue their matter though another route such as Early Conciliation or the civil court.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-04-26T10:19:40.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723065/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723065/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723065/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-04-20","Pay: Complaints","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answer of 20 April 2017 to Question 70317, what the total number of complaints of failure to pay wages received by ACAS was in April 2016 to March 2017.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","71511"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723068","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-04-25","<p>Information on the number of complaints of pregnancy and maternity related discrimination in the Employment Tribunals is published in the MoJ statistical bulletin, “Tribunals and gender recognition statistics quarterly”. The latest bulletin, for the quarter October to December 2016, is available at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/tribunals-and-gender-recognition-certificate-statistics-quarterly-october-to-december-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/tribunals-and-gender-recognition-certificate-statistics-quarterly-october-to-december-2016</a></p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2017-04-25T14:38:42.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723068/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723068/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723068/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-04-20","Pregnancy: Discrimination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate she has made of the number of maternity and pregnancy discrimination-related claims in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","71448"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723069","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-04-25","<p>The Office of the Director of Labour Market Enforcement is jointly funded by the Home Office and the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy. The scope of the Director’s work may vary over time. We have agreed an annual approach to budget setting in line with a forecast submitted by the Director’s Office. The Director is in the process of finalising his forecast for 2017/18. Funding for his office will be maintained in the meantime.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-04-25T13:07:42.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723069/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723069/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723069/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-04-20","Director of Labour Market Enforcement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answer of 18 April 2017 to Question 69883, what operating budget has been set for the Office of the Director of Labour Market Enforcement in (a) 2017-18, (b) 2018-19 and (c) 2019-20.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","71478"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723070","Department for International Trade","false","2017-04-26","<p>The Department for International Trade, including UK Export Finance, have had 22 staff seconded to the department from outside the Civil Service in the last six months.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-04-26T11:38:34.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723070/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723070/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723070/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-04-20","Department for International Trade: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many staff have been seconded into his Department from outside the Civil Service in the last six months.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","71439"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723071","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-04-25","<p>Since the EU referendum, Ministers from across Government have met civil society organisations and businesses from every sector. Ministers from the Department for Exiting the European Union have played an active part in this effort, engaging with businesses in every sector cluster and visiting every region of the UK, including Bristol, to hear and understand their priorities for our exit negotiations. This is part of our commitment to build a national consensus on our negotiating position. Government has regular engagement with the core cities as part of its wider work with local communities and organisations.</p><p>Details of Ministerial meetings are published in the Department for Exiting the European Union’s quarterly Transparency Returns, which are made publicly available on Gov.uk.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-04-25T17:01:30.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723071/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723071/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723071/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-04-20","Business: Bristol","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what discussions he has had with businesses in Bristol on (a) ending freedom of movement, (b) withdrawing from the EU single market and (c) their priorities for the Government's negotiations of the UK leaving the EU; and what research he has commissioned into the potential effect of the UK leaving the EU on the UK's core cities.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","71487"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723072","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-04-27","<p>The department has sourced a large proportion of experienced staff from across Whitehall and a number of secondees from the private sector and the wider public sector. We are not in a position to give a final total for particular groups of staff as recruitment is ongoing and numbers are regularly changing.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-04-27T09:22:25.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723072/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723072/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723072/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-04-20","Department for Exiting the European Union: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many staff have been seconded to his Department from outside the Civil Service in the last six months.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","71438"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723073","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-04-27","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to the hon. Member in the time available before Prorogation.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-04-27T09:26:36.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723073/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723073/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723073/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-04-20","European Medicines Agency: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many people are employed by the European Medicines Agency; and how many of those people are British citizens.","false","Biography information for James Berry","Kingston and Surbiton","James Berry","71445"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723074","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-04-27","<p>Data relating to the total number of employees working for the European Banking Authority can be found on their website: <a href="http://www.eba.europa.eu/about-us/careers/multimedia/eba-at-glance" target="_blank">http://www.eba.europa.eu/about-us/careers/multimedia/eba-at-glance</a>.</p><p>Current data relating to the nationality of employees of the European Banking Authority is not available.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-04-27T09:23:31.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723074/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723074/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723074/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-04-20","European Banking Authority: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many people are employed by the European Banking Authority; and how many of those people are British citizens.","false","Biography information for James Berry","Kingston and Surbiton","James Berry","71443"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723075","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Government has been clear that we should always put citizens first. This was reflected in the Prime Minister’s letter to the President of the European Council confirming the Government’s decision to invoke Article 50. We want to strike an early agreement about the rights of EU nationals in the UK and UK nationals in the EU and we would have been happy to do so in advance of negotiations. We will look to prioritise these issues as soon as negotiations begin.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-04-27T09:18:41.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723075/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723075/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723075/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-04-20","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what progress his Department has made in securing a reciprocal agreement with the EU that guarantees existing rights of (a) EU nationals in the UK and (b) UK nationals in the EU after the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","71429"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723076","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-04-26","<p>There is high public interest in the government making sure that the UK remains as stable as possible throughout our exit from the EU. Disclosure of fragments of commercially or politically sensitive information may mean future discussions will not take place, or will not take place with the same frankness as before. The department has no plans to change policy regarding the publication of correspondence.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-04-26T15:55:43.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723076/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723076/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723076/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-04-20","Department for Exiting the European Union: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, if he will publish all official correspondence between his Department and the Scottish Government since 1 March 2017.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","71519"
