"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722420","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-24","<p>At Budget 17, the Office for Budget Responsibility forecast public sector net debt to be 88.8% of GDP – £1829.7bn – at the end of the financial year 2017-18.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2017-04-24T13:55:44.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722420/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722420/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722420/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-04-19","Public Sector Debt","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of public sector net debt at the end of the current financial year.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","71229"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722421","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-24","<p>I refer the honourable member for Linlithgow and East Falkirk to the answer given on 24 April 2017 to his previous question on this subject.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-04-24T14:35:26.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722421/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722421/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722421/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-04-19","Taxation: Landlords","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the potential effect of taxing landlords on their income rather than profit on the cost of rent for tenants.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","71284"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722422","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-24","<p>Changes to staffing levels within HM Revenue and Customs will be dependent on the outcome of EU exit negotiations.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-04-24T12:02:50.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722422/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722422/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722422/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-04-19","Revenue and Customs: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans he has to increase staffing levels in HM Revenue and Customs after the UK has left the EU and EU customs union.","true","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","71300"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722423","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-25","<p>This information is not available. The data that HM Revenue and Customs hold on charitable donations and associated tax reliefs cannot be broken down into such sector specific details.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-04-25T10:47:27.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722423/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722423/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722423/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-04-19","Tax Allowances: Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much tax and business rates private and public schools saved as a result of their charitable status in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","71234"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722424","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-24","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) considers requests for ACAS Early Conciliations with an open mind and on a case by case basis, in consultation with ACAS. If a particular case has already gone through a robust internal appeal process, or is still going through HMRC internal procedures, then a request for Early Conciliation is likely to be declined.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-04-24T12:06:50.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722424/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722424/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722424/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-04-19","ACAS","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the policy of HM Revenue and Customs is on requests for ACAS Early Conciliations made by its employees who are seeking to resolve workplace disputes.","true","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","71244"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722426","Church Commissioners","false","2017-04-24","<p>At parish and diocesan level the Church is closely involved in providing support to homeless people through night shelters and other activities, and raising funds and awareness. Recently in the House of Lords bishops supported the Homelessness Reduction Bill.</p><p>In the Torbay area the Vicar on the Streets initiative undertaken by Revd Gary Deighton of St George's Church, Goodrington, and the Winter Night Shelter run by local churches have both made a real difference to the issues of homelessness. The clergy and parishioners of Goodrington and Torbay have raised nearly five thousand pounds over the period of Lent to support the Shekinah Mission, which works across Devon to provide a safe space for people to develop their skills, regain their self-worth and go on to live independent and fulfilling lives.</p>","Meriden","Dame Caroline Spelman",,"2017-04-24T10:03:04.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722426/answer","Biography information for Dame Caroline Spelman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722426/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722426/answer",,,,,"9","Church Commissioners","Church Commissioners","2017-04-19","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the right hon. Member for Meriden, representing the Church Commissioners, what steps the Church of England is taking to support local projects tackling homelessness.","false","Biography information for Kevin Foster","Torbay","Kevin Foster","71313"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722428","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-04-24","<p>The Department estimates that 16,000 businesses will benefit from the targeted support for Small Business Rate Relief recipients measure announced at Budget 2017. The Department does not hold the data required to provide a breakdown by region, constituency or local authority.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-04-24T16:31:32.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722428/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722428/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722428/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-04-19","Small Businesses: Non-domestic Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many businesses will benefit from the targeted support for Small Business Rate Relief measure in Budget 2017; and what the breakdown by (a) region, (b) constituency and (c) local authority of those businesses will be.","false","Biography information for Teresa Pearce","Erith and Thamesmead","Teresa Pearce","71336"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722429","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-04-24","<p>The Department publishes a detailed description of the methodology used to calculate the household projections, which can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/2014-based-household-projections-methodology" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/2014-based-household-projections-methodology</a></p><p>It should be noted that as of 23 January 2017, the responsibility for the household projections has been transferred to the Office for National Statistics, who are responsible for all future publications.</p><p> </p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-04-24T14:28:21.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722429/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722429/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722429/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-04-19","Households","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how his Department calculated household projections provided in its publication, 2014-based household projections in England, 2014 to 2039.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","71390"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722430","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-04-24","<p>The information is not centrally held in the form requested and could only be provided at disproportionate cost. Funding is generally not allocated by Parliamentary constituency.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-04-24T16:28:57.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722430/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722430/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722430/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-04-19","Department for Communities and Local Government: North Herefordshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much his Department has spent in North Herefordshire constituency since 2015.","false","Biography information for Bill Wiggin","North Herefordshire","Bill Wiggin","71373"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722431","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-04-24","<p>Under the Housing and Planning Act 2016 local authorities can be required to make a payment in respect of their higher value housing that is expected to become vacant in any year. The legislation requires various statutory processes to be followed, including consulting representatives of local government and relevant professional bodies before issuing a determination, setting out local authorities’ payments. Local authorities will not be required to make a payment in respect of their higher value vacant housing in 2017/18.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-04-24T15:55:25.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722431/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722431/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722431/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-04-19","Council Housing: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will proceed with the forced sale of council homes and other assets to fund the Right to Buy.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","71362"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722432","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-04-24","<p>Figures are not available at constituency level.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-04-24T15:56:16.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722432/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722432/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722432/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-04-19","Council Housing: West Bromwich East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many people are on the waiting list for council housing in West Bromwich East constituency.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","71268"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722433","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-04-24","<p>The Department does not produce constituency level estimates.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-04-24T15:55:47.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722433/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722433/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722433/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-04-19","Private Rented Housing: West Bromwich East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what proportion of tenants in West Bromwich East constituency live in private rented accommodation.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","71270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722434","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-04-24","<p>The number of additional affordable homes are available at local authority level in live table 1008 published on the departments website.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-affordable-housing-supply" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-affordable-housing-supply</a></p><p>As outlined in the Written Ministerial Statement of 18 September 2012, <em>Official Report</em>, Column 32WS, my department no longer publishes statistics by government office region. Local authority figures from which regional estimates can be calculated can be found in live table 1008.</p><p> </p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-04-24T14:27:38.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722434/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722434/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722434/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-04-19","Affordable Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many affordable homes were completed in each of the last seven years in (a) England and (b) each region.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","71246"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722435","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-04-24","<p>Our White Paper<em>: Fixing our Broken Housing Market</em> sets out the Government’s ambition to support more people into home ownership through a range of products, including shared ownership, rent-to-buy and starter homes. We have made strong progress by developing a framework for starter homes through the Housing and Planning Act 2016; delivering planning reforms; and making a £1.2 billion starter homes land fund available.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-04-24T15:56:56.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722435/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722435/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722435/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-04-19","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many starter homes he expects to be completed by 8 June 2017.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","71247"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722436","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-04-26","<p>While we recognise that the housing market is different throughout England, evidence shows that concerns associated with letting agents charging fees to tenants are prevalent across the whole country, not just particular regions. Our consultation exercise also seeks evidence to inform the future approach.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-04-26T10:50:32.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722436/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722436/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722436/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-04-19","Letting Agents: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he made of disparities in regional housing markets prior to publishing the consultation paper, Banning letting agent fees paid by tenants, published on 7 April 2017.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","71226"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722439","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-04-25","<p>In December 2016, the Institute for Public Policy Research published a report on the cost to Government associated with problem gamblers (commissioned by GambleAware). The Report can be found at: http://www.ippr.org/publications/cards-on-the-table</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-04-25T14:25:31.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722439/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722439/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722439/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-04-19","Gambling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate she has made of the cost of problem gambling to the Government.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","71253"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722440","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-04-25","<p>A review of gaming machines and social responsibility measures was launched in October 2016, which included a look at the issue of B2 gaming machines (more commonly known as fixed odds betting terminals). Responses to the review’s call for evidence are currently being considered and a response will be published in due course.</p><p> </p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","71286","2017-04-25T14:27:16.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722440/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722440/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722440/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-04-19","Gaming Machines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment she has made of the effectiveness of player protection measures for fixed odds betting terminals.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","71254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722441","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-04-26","<p>Ofcom estimates that 98.5% of UK households have access to around 18 channels including those from the public service broadcasters (PSBs) on the digital terrestrial TV (DTT, or Freeview) platform. Around 90% of UK households are also able to receive additional commercial DTT channels. Around 1.5% of UK households cannot easily receive DTT services with less than 0.5% not able to receive DTT services at all. However, DTT, cable and satellite digital television services together cover practically 100% of UK households, so that in all but the most exceptional of cases, everyone, including homes in hard to reach areas, should be able to get digital television services. As well as subscription services, digital satellite TV offers non-subscription reception options for a one-off equipment and installation cost, but with no on-going monthly payments. This includes FreeSat free-to-view satellite service which was launched by the BBC and ITV in 2008.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-04-26T09:09:54.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722441/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722441/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722441/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-04-19","Television: Broadcasting Reception","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what progress has been made in improving terrestrial television coverage in (a) Blaenau Gwent and (b) other areas of the UK to ensure that all households have access to basic channels without needing to purchase a satellite dish.","false","Biography information for Nick Smith","Blaenau Gwent","Nick Smith","71314"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722442","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-04-25","<p>A review of gaming machines and social responsibility measures was launched in October 2016, which included a look at the issue of B2 gaming machines (more commonly known as fixed odds betting terminals). Responses to the review’s call for evidence are currently being considered and a response will be published in due course.</p><p> </p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","71254","2017-04-25T14:27:16.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722442/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722442/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722442/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-04-19","Gaming Machines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, when she plans to announce the findings of her Department's review of stakes and prizes for gaming machines.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","71286"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722443","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-04-26","<p>We will shortly agree the specifics of each of the 70 projects that successfully applied to the Tampon Tax Fund this year, to ensure that taxpayers' money is put to the best use. We will only make grants where we are 100% certain that they align with the aims of the fund.</p><p> </p><p>All applications into the fund were assessed by officials against three criteria: evidence for the need of the project: the organisation’s ability to deliver; and the sustainability/impact of the project, and were then vetted by officials before they were signed off.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson","71354","2017-04-26T14:44:44.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722443/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722443/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722443/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-04-19","LIFE","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment her Department made of the charity, Life's patient information literature before awarding it a grant from the Tampon Tax Fund.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","71353"
