"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722448","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-25","<p>The projected Initial Operating Capability for the integration of Brimstone 2 on Typhoon is December 2018 and we remain on track to achieve that date.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-04-25T11:32:05.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722448/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722448/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722448/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-04-19","European Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the projected Initial Operating Capability date is for the Brimstone 2 missile on the Typhoon aircraft.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","71349"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722449","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-25","<p>It took six years and two months to achieve Initial Operating Capability for the Brimstone 2 missile on Tornado which came into effect in May 2016.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-04-25T11:34:06.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722449/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722449/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722449/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-04-19","Tornado Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how long it took to achieve Initial Operating Capability for the Brimstone 2 missile on the Tornado aircraft.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","71350"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722450","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-25","<p>The Ministry of Defence, with Leonardo Helicopters, are jointly funding an £8 million capability concept demonstrator for future Rotary Wing Unmanned Air Systems. It will inform all Front Line Commands of how emerging unmanned rotary wing technologies might contribute to the future battle space. This work will be conducted over the next 12 to 18 months and builds on a number of earlier activities, including further demonstration of autonomous landing capabilities.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-04-25T11:33:38.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722450/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722450/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722450/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-04-19","Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will provide details of the contract for Phase II of the rotary wing unmanned air system, capability concept demonstrator, awarded to Leonardo helicopters.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","71351"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722451","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-24","<p>The value of direct contracts in financial year (FY) 2014-15, where the billing address is identified as in North Herefordshire is, £1,792,814. In FY 2015-16 the value is £857,964. The data for 2016-17 is not yet available.</p><p> </p><p>No adjustment has been made for contracts, such as enabling contracts, which may cover the whole of the Ministry of Defence (MOD) estate. The figures and this methodology do not therefore give a full representation of the amount of work truly undertaken in North Herefordshire.</p><p> </p><p>A summary of MOD regional expenditure with UK industry and supported employment 2015-16 can be found here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/mod-regional-expenditure-with-uk-industry-and-supported-employment-index" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/mod-regional-expenditure-with-uk-industry-and-supported-employment-index</a></p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-04-24T15:25:18.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722451/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722451/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722451/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-04-19","Ministry of Defence: North Herefordshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department has spent in North Herefordshire constituency since 2015.","false","Biography information for Bill Wiggin","North Herefordshire","Bill Wiggin","71370"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722452","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-25","<p>The United Kingdom did not participate in the Royal Australian Navy exercise Ocean Explorer.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-04-25T11:31:27.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722452/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722452/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722452/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-04-19","Military Exercises: Australia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) assets and (b) personnel from his Department took part in Royal Australian Navy exercise Ocean Explorer off the coast of Western Australia.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","71348"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722453","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-25","<p>We value the support and contribution made by trade unions. Following on from Sir John Parker's trade union engagement prior to publishing his independent report, we have continued to keep trade unions involved as we develop the UK national shipbuilding strategy. Representatives from the Confederation of Shipbuilding and Engineering Unions (CSEU) and GMB have attended Industry stakeholder events. We also undertook a briefing on the shipbuilding strategy followed by a question and answer session at the CSEU Maritime Forum on 13 February 2017.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-04-25T11:34:35.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722453/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722453/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722453/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-04-19","Warships: Shipbuilding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what consultations have taken place with the relevant trade unions on the National Shipbuilding Strategy in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","71263"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722454","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-25","<p>Over the last year, the Royal Navy has continued to meet all their standing commitments, delivering a strong presence at home and globally in protecting our national interests. These include: Continuous at Sea Deterrent; Fleet Ready Escort; Towed Array Patrol Ship; marine enforcement; mine countermeasures support; Atlantic Patrol Tasking North and South; Gibraltar Squadron; operations East of Suez; contributing to the Joint Expeditionary Force (Maritime) and Standing NATO Response Force; supporting EU and NATO counter-migration operations in the Mediterranean and Aegean Sea.</p><p>The Royal Navy will continue to take part in a wide range of national and international exercises and deployments in 2018 to ensure that our forces are ready to undertake a range of activities to meet the challenges of an uncertain world. I am withholding the details of future deployments and exercises as release would, or would be likely to, prejudice the security and safety of our Armed Forces.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-04-25T13:50:28.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722454/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722454/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722454/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-04-19","Navy: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what (a) operational and (b) other targets and objectives the Royal Navy met during the last 12 months; what major deployments and exercises are planned for the Royal Navy in 2018; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","71223"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722455","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-24","<p>Incidents requiring explosive ordnance disposal experts in Northern Ireland are dealt with solely by military personnel. Between 1 January and 31 March 2017 explosive ordnance disposal personnel have responded to 59 incidents in Northern Ireland.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-04-24T15:25:51.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722455/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722455/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722455/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-04-19","Bomb Disposal: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, on how many occasions explosive ordnance disposal personnel were deployed in Northern Ireland between 1 January and 31 March 2017.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","71232"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722456","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-25","<p>The Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 made provision to augment the Queen Elizabeth Class Aircraft Carriers and maximise their ability to support our amphibious operations. Together with the existing amphibious ships of the Royal Navy and the Royal Fleet Auxiliary, this will provide the capability to deploy our amphibious forces.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-04-25T11:32:58.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722456/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722456/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722456/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-04-19","Amphibious Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to paragraph 1.12 of the National Audit Office report, Delivering Carrier Strike, published on 16 March 2017, what contingencies his Department is considering to provide ship to shore amphibious operations after the decommissioning of HMS Ocean in 2018.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","71236"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722457","Department for Education","false","2017-04-27","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>The information requested is not available. The Student Loans Company does not publish nor forecast the number of student loan borrowers by parliamentary constituency.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-04-27T08:11:57.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722457/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722457/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722457/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-04-19","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many graduates in each parliamentary constituency will be affected by the decision to freeze the student loan repayment threshold in each year from 2016.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","71248"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722458","Department for Education","false","2017-04-24","<p>Helping all young people to get the careers education and guidance they need to climb the ladder of opportunity is crucial to delivering real social justice. We are investing £90m over this Parliament to ensure that every young person has equal access to the life-changing advice and inspiration that they need to fulfil their potential and succeed in life. This includes funding for The Careers &amp; Enterprise Company to continue the excellent work it has started to transform the provision of careers, enterprise and employer engagement experiences for young people.</p><p>Based on the most recent data, the Company’s Enterprise Adviser Network is now active in 37 out of the 38 Local Enterprise Partnership areas. 1,618 secondary schools and colleges across the country have signed up to the network and 1,422 Enterprise Advisers are working with them. In Shropshire, 13 secondary schools are signed up to the Enterprise Adviser Network, of which 10 are matched with an Enterprise Adviser and 3 are due to be matched.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Harlow","Robert Halfon",,"2017-04-24T15:03:27.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722458/answer","Biography information for Robert Halfon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722458/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722458/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-04-19","Schools: Shropshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many Shropshire Council secondary schools have an allocated Careers and Enterprise Company adviser.","false","Biography information for Daniel Kawczynski","Shrewsbury and Atcham","Daniel Kawczynski","71239"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722459","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-04-26","<p>The Government is fully committed to maintaining the UK’s world-leading science, research and higher education base.</p><p> </p><p>According to Higher Education Statistics Agency (HESA) data, eleven institutions in the West Midlands, which includes the Universities of Warwick; Birmingham; and Aston, received public research funding from Higher Education Funding Council for England and the Research Councils totalling £188 million in 2015/16.</p><p> </p><p>The Autumn Statement 2016 announcement of an extra £2 billion a year in research and development by 2020-21 underlines the place of science and innovation at the heart of this Government’s industrial strategy.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-04-26T10:19:19.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722459/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722459/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722459/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-04-19","Research: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps he is taking to support investment in science research at universities in the West Midlands.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","71241"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722460","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Government is fully committed to maintaining the UK’s world-leading science, research and higher education base.</p><p> </p><p>According to Higher Education Statistics Agency (HESA) data the University of Warwick and Coventry University received public research funding from Higher Education Funding Council for England and the Research Councils of £72.6 million and £4.32 million respectively in 2015/16.</p><p> </p><p>The Autumn Statement 2016 announcement of an extra £2 billion a year in research and development by 2020-21 underlines the place of science and innovation at the heart of this Government’s industrial strategy.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-04-27T13:41:38.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722460/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722460/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722460/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-04-19","Research: Coventry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps he is taking to support investment in science research at universities in Coventry.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","71242"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722461","Department for Education","false","2017-04-24","<p>The open consultation on Analysing family circumstances and education provided a range of supporting analysis. Supplementary tables with additional analysis will be published by the department as part of the consultation response.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2017-04-24T16:39:22.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722461/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722461/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722461/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-04-19","Pupils: Grammar Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to the supplementary tables published alongside her Department's consultation, Analysing family circumstances and education, what proportion of pupils listed as attending selective schools who are not disadvantaged are in households of incomes of (a) £0 to £10,000, (b) £10,000 to £15,000, (c) £15,000 to £20,000, (d) £20,000 to £25,000, (e) £25,000 to £31,000, (f) £31,000 to £38,000, (g) £38,000 to £47,000, (h) £47,000 to £59,000 (i) £59,000 to £78,000 and (j) greater than £78,000.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","71271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722462","Department for Education","false","2017-04-24","<p>The data are in the public domain and can be sourced at the following location:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/16-to-19-education-funding-allocations#published-allocations" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/guidance/16-to-19-education-funding-allocations#published-allocations</a></p><p>71279 - we do not hold constituency details for institutions so are unable to provide the required information for Coventry South so the above shows data for Coventry local authority as a whole.</p><p>71280 - the data provided for West Midlands consists of those local authorities that are grouped into the EFA region West Midlands.</p><p>16-19 funding operates under a lagged funding methodology which uses historic funding factors and student numbers to calculate a funding allocation for each of our c.3,300 funded institutions for each academic year.</p><p>With the exception of c.150 commercial and charitable providers we do not reconcile institutions’ allocated funding to their actual expenditure or funding earned, so we do not operate post 16 funding on the basis of planned and actual expenditure.</p><p>The figures quoted above represent the actual allocations made to institutions for the stated academic years, based on the lagged principle explained above.</p>","Harlow","Robert Halfon","71280","2017-04-24T15:04:29.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722462/answer","Biography information for Robert Halfon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722462/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722462/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-04-19","Further Education: Coventry South","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the (a) planned and (b) actual expenditure on 16 to 19 education provision was in each of the last three years in Coventry South constituency.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","71279"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722463","Department for Education","false","2017-04-24","<p>The data are in the public domain and can be sourced at the following location:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/16-to-19-education-funding-allocations#published-allocations" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/guidance/16-to-19-education-funding-allocations#published-allocations</a></p><p>71279 - we do not hold constituency details for institutions so are unable to provide the required information for Coventry South so the above shows data for Coventry local authority as a whole.</p><p>71280 - the data provided for West Midlands consists of those local authorities that are grouped into the EFA region West Midlands.</p><p>16-19 funding operates under a lagged funding methodology which uses historic funding factors and student numbers to calculate a funding allocation for each of our c.3,300 funded institutions for each academic year.</p><p>With the exception of c.150 commercial and charitable providers we do not reconcile institutions’ allocated funding to their actual expenditure or funding earned, so we do not operate post 16 funding on the basis of planned and actual expenditure.</p><p>The figures quoted above represent the actual allocations made to institutions for the stated academic years, based on the lagged principle explained above.</p>","Harlow","Robert Halfon","71279","2017-04-24T15:04:29.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722463/answer","Biography information for Robert Halfon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722463/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722463/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-04-19","Further Education: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the (a) planned and (b) actual expenditure on 16 to 19 education provision was in each of the last three years in the West Midlands.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","71280"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722464","Department for Education","false","2017-04-24","<p>This information is published in the statistical publication available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/schools-pupils-and-their-characteristics-january-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/schools-pupils-and-their-characteristics-january-2016</a></p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2017-04-24T14:37:04.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722464/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722464/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722464/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-04-19","Free School Meals: West Bromwich East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many school children in West Bromwich East constituency are not eligible for free school meals.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","71267"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722465","Department for Education","false","2017-04-24","<p>The Department’s guidance to schools makes clear that when recruiting staff, employers and governing bodies must be aware of their responsibilities set out in the Equality Act 2010. Schools must not discriminate directly or indirectly against any prospective employee on the basis of any protected characteristic (including age, race, sex or disability) in relation to appointments, pay and conditions.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-04-24T14:18:42.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722465/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722465/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722465/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-04-19","Teachers: Older People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps she is taking to ensure that schools do not intentionally or unintentionally discriminate against teachers aged over 60 years who apply for jobs.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","71296"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722466","Department for Education","false","2017-04-24","<p>The Chief Social Worker has met social workers and other individuals and organisations at many meetings, events and conferences to discuss policy and the Children and Social Work Bill more broadly, where the power may have been only one possible area of discussion. Below is a list of the key meetings attended by the CSW, which focussed more specifically on the power to test different ways of working.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Date of meeting</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Organisation/Individual</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>25/07/2016</p></td><td><p>Family Rights Group</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>01/08/2016</p></td><td><p>Family Rights Group</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>03/08/2016</p></td><td><p>Cafcass</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>04/08/2016</p></td><td><p>Who Cares? Trust</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>08/09/2016</p></td><td><p>Barnardo’s</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>08/09/2016</p></td><td><p>NSPCC</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>13/09/2016</p></td><td><p>Partners in Practice Local Authorities (Hampshire County Council, Leeds City Council, Lincolnshire County Council); Baroness Pinnock; Earl of Listowel</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>15/09/2016</p></td><td><p>Article 39</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>27/09/2016</p></td><td><p>Lord Laming</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>12/10/2016</p></td><td><p>The Children’s Society</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>16/01/2017</p></td><td><p>NAIRO; Hampshire County Council; Tri-borough Children’s Services; Leeds City Council; North Yorkshire County Council</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>21/02/2017</p></td><td><p>Tim Loughton MP; Kelly Tollhurst MP; Lord Mackay; Lord Laming</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2017-04-24T14:35:58.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722466/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722466/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722466/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-04-19","Children: Social Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will disclose names of individuals and organisations who attended meetings with the Chief Social Worker for Children and Families on the power to test different ways of working provisions of the Children and Social Work Bill; and on what dates such meetings took place.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","71298"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722467","Department for Education","false","2017-04-24","<p>The Department has taken action to improve its processes in the handling of potential conflicts of interests. There is a clear process for all civil servants to follow. Specifically, there is an agreed protocol in place that specifies the Chief Social Worker will not be involved in any decision-making process, which could result in any public funding being awarded to Morning Lane Associates or any other organisations in which she may have a conflict of interest. This sets out proportionate measures to ensure there are no actual or perceived conflicts of interest around funding decisions, while still allowing the Chief Social Worker to fulfil her role.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2017-04-24T16:38:29.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722467/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722467/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722467/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-04-19","Children: Social Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what action was taken by her Department in response to the National Audit Office's investigation into a potential conflict of interest between the Chief Social Worker for Children and Families and a company called Morning Lane Associates.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","71299"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722468","Department for Education","false","2017-04-27","<p>Information by Westminster Constituency or English region on the number of children aged over five receiving subsidised milk under the scheme is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>With regard to the longer-term approach to school milk provision, I refer the hon. Member to the government’s answer to parliamentary question 60828 on 25 January 2017.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","71309","2017-04-27T07:37:12.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722468/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722468/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722468/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-04-19","School Milk: Garston and Halewood","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many schools in Garston and Halewood constituency receive subsidised milk under the European School Milk Scheme.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","71308"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722469","Department for Education","false","2017-04-27","<p>Information by Westminster Constituency or English region on the number of children aged over five receiving subsidised milk under the scheme is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>With regard to the longer-term approach to school milk provision, I refer the hon. Member to the government’s answer to parliamentary question 60828 on 25 January 2017.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","71308","2017-04-27T07:37:12.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722469/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722469/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722469/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-04-19","School Milk","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what plans she has to replace the funding of subsidised milk provided under the European School Milk Scheme after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","71309"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722470","Department for Education","false","2017-04-27","<p>This government wants pupils to be healthy. It promotes the consumption of dairy products as part of a balanced diet through guidance, funding and legislation.</p><p> </p><p>The School Food Standards (where they apply) provide the legislative framework to ensure schools provide children with healthy food and drink options. This includes a requirement to make milk available at least once during the school day. The majority of schools are subject to the School Food Standards. However, some academies and free schools are not. As part of our work on the childhood obesity plan, we will be encouraging all schools to commit to the standards.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The Department does not hold information on how many schools in Garston and Halewood constituency comply with the milk requirements of the School Food Standards.</p><p> </p><p>As indicated in ‘Childhood Obesity: a plan for action’, we will update the School Food Standards in light of refreshed government dietary recommendations. We plan to make further information on this work available later in the year. As stated in my answer to parliamentary question 64266, the revised Eatwell guide is distributed to schools to use alongside the school food standards and continues to define the government’s recommendations on a healthy balanced diet.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","71303 ; 71305 ; 71306","2017-04-27T07:31:45.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722470/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722470/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722470/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-04-19","Schools: Milk","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps her Department is taking to ensure that all schools comply with the milk requirements of the standards for school food in England, published on 9 September 2016.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","71302"
