"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722522","Home Office","false","2017-04-25","<p>The estimated average cost of processing nationality naturalisation and registration applications in each year since 2015 is detailed within the appropriate publications below:</p><p> </p><p>Naturalisation</p><p>2015/16</p><p><a href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2015/768/pdfs/uksiem_20150768_en.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2015/768/pdfs/uksiem_20150768_en.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>2016/17</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/503759/2016_Unit_Costs_Table.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/503759/2016_Unit_Costs_Table.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>2017/18</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/606616/Unit_cost_table_2017.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/606616/Unit_cost_table_2017.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>Registration</p><p>2015/16</p><p><a href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2015/768/pdfs/uksiem_20150768_en.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2015/768/pdfs/uksiem_20150768_en.pdf</a></p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-04-25T12:26:02.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722522/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722522/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722522/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-19","British Nationality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the average cost to her Department was of administering applications for (a) naturalisation (b) registration to become a British citizen in each year since 2015.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","71318"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722523","Home Office","false","2017-04-24","<p>No statistical information is available showing how many applications for British citizenship have been rejected or accepted where the applicant had been made bankrupt.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-04-24T13:45:17.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722523/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722523/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722523/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-19","British Nationality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many applications for naturalisation to become a British citizen were (a) rejected on the grounds that the applicant was made bankrupt within 10 years of making the application and (b) accepted despite the applicant being bankrupt within 10 years of making the application in each year since 2015.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","71319"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722524","Department for International Development","false","2017-04-24","<p>The UK provided £112 million in aid to Yemen in 2016/17, which supported over 462,000 people with food or food vouchers, and over 889,000 women and children with nutrition interventions. Given the scale of the current crisis in Yemen, yesterday we further increased UK aid for 2017/18 to £139 million, to provide lifesaving aid to hundreds of thousands of desperate people. I would refer the Right Honourable Gentleman to the Written Ministerial Statement HCWS606 for further information.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-04-24T16:53:50.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722524/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722524/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722524/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-04-19","Yemen: Famine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, with reference to the UN report stating that 60 per cent of Yemenis are in crisis or emergency food situations, published on 15 March 2017, what steps her Department is taking to prevent famine in Yemen.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","71294"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722525","Department for International Development","false","2017-04-24","<p>The Department will liaise with CADANI (Coalition of Aid and Development Agencies in Northern Ireland) as well as other appropriate Organisations in order to promote the Small Charities Challenge Fund.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2017-04-24T15:24:44.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722525/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722525/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722525/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-04-19","Charities: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps she has taken to promote take-up of her Department's small charities fund among charities in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","71228"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722526","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-04-24","<p>We have been carrying out a comprehensive review of the probation system to improve outcomes for offenders and communities while making sure public protection remains our top priority. The review is considering all aspects of the probation system, including performance and contractual arrangements. We intend to set out our next steps in due course.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-04-24T16:18:48.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722526/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722526/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722526/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-04-19","Probation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if she will publish the conclusions of her Department's Probation Services Review.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","71277"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722527","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-04-24","<p>Her Majesty’s Prison and Probation Service, through the Probation System Review, has been working proactively with all Community Rehabilitation Companies. The review has been looking at both the contractual arrangements and the effectiveness of service delivery.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-04-24T16:21:05.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722527/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722527/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722527/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-04-19","Community Rehabilitation Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what changes have been made to the provisions governing (a) charging levels, (b) fee levels and (c) reward mechanisms in the contracts between her Department and community rehabilitation companies which are planned to take effect in 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","71278"
