"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722190","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-04-26","<p>This government has no such plans, but in our Housing White Paper we set out a range of measures to speed up build out. The consultation is currently open.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-04-26T14:01:10.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722190/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722190/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722190/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-04-18","Housing: Planning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will grant to local authorities the power to levy council tax on developments not completed within a set period.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","71207"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722191","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-04-27","<p>Such estimates can be calculated using publically available HM Land Registry Price Paid Data but it is a complex exercise that would not be completed before Parliament prorogues.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-04-27T11:31:15.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722191/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722191/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722191/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-04-18","Leasehold: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what recent estimate he has made of the ratio of the average prices paid for newbuild leasehold houses compared with newbuild freehold houses in (a) Gateshead, (b) London, (c) Wigan, (d) Manchester, (e) Bootle, (f) Liverpool and (g) Runcorn.","false","Biography information for Sir Peter Bottomley","Worthing West","Sir Peter Bottomley","71212"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722192","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-04-26","<p>We will shortly agree the specifics of each of the 70 projects that successfully applied to the Tampon Tax Fund this year, to ensure that taxpayers' money is put to the best use. We will only make grants where we are 100% certain that they align with the aims of the fund.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson","71100 ; 71120 ; 71122 ; 71123 ; 71170","2017-04-26T09:30:49.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722192/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722192/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722192/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-04-18","LIFE","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if she will review the decision to award the anti-abortion charity, Life, a grant from the Tampon Tax Fund.","false","Biography information for Sarah Champion","Rotherham","Sarah Champion","71186"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722193","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-04-24","<p>My department has allocated around a third of the full time equivalent (FTE) of a Band A and half of a FTE Band B staff to work on the Youth Policy Statement since November 2016. This has included engaging with young people and the youth sector through a series of workshops. The proportion of time staff spent on the Youth Policy Statement is subject to change as the work develops.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson","70881","2017-04-24T14:17:45.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722193/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722193/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722193/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-04-18","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what (a) staff, at what salary cost, and (b) other resources have been committed by her Department in preparing the forthcoming Youth Policy Statement.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","71202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722194","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-04-26","<p>The latest figures are for 2016 regional NCS programme costs, broken down by region against seasons (Spring, Summer and Autumn) in the attached table. These figures take into account provider costs exclusively which vary depending on provider.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2017-04-26T14:35:26.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722194/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722194/answer","2016 regional NCS programme costs.docx","2016 regional NCS programme costs.docx","2016 regional NCS programme costs","2016 regional NCS programme costs","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722194/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-04-18","Voluntary Work: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 5 April 2017 to Question 69622, on voluntary work: young people, how much of NCSs expenditure occurred in each region of the UK in the latest period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","71187"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722195","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-04-26","<p>We will shortly agree the specifics of each of the 70 projects that successfully applied to the Tampon Tax Fund this year, to ensure that taxpayers' money is put to the best use. We will only make grants where we are 100% certain that they align with the aims of the fund.</p><p> </p><p>It would not be appropriate to publish details of individual applications in advance of grants being made. All applications into the fund were assessed by officials against three criteria: evidence for the need of the project: the organisation’s ability to deliver; and the sustainability/impact of the project.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2017-04-26T09:28:26.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722195/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722195/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722195/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-04-18","LIFE","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if she will publish the (a) Tampon Tax Fund application submitted by the charity, Life and (b) criteria for awarding grants from the Tampon Tax Fund.","false","Biography information for Sarah Champion","Rotherham","Sarah Champion","71180"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722196","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-04-26","<p>We will shortly agree the specifics of each of the 70 projects that successfully applied to the Tampon Tax Fund this year, to ensure that taxpayers' money is put to the best use. We will only make grants where we are 100% certain that they align with the aims of the fund.</p><p> </p><p>All applications into the fund were assessed by officials against three criteria: evidence for the need of the project: the organisation’s ability to deliver; and the sustainability/impact of the project, and were then vetted by officials before they were signed off.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2017-04-26T14:42:02.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722196/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722196/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722196/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-04-18","Sanitary Protection: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the stages are in the application process for the Tampon Tax Fund; and whether the Minister for Civil Society approves each grant decision.","false","Biography information for Sarah Champion","Rotherham","Sarah Champion","71181"
